2. ARGO WORKFLOW DAG YAML
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  k8s/argo/flowforge-pipeline.yaml:
    - Defines Workflow with entrypoint flowforge-dag, SA flowforge-workflow, TTL strategy and parameters:
      snapshot-id, repo-urls, log-time-range, run-gnn.
    - DAG tasks map to pipeline stages:
      clone-repos, fetch-logs, fetch-manifests → parse-code/parse-logs/parse-topology →
      index-opensearch, build-knowledge-graph → detect-anomalies, mine-sequences →
      embed-code/embed-logs (GPU) → optional gnn-analysis (when run-gnn) →
      classify-migration → build-candidates → synthesize → publish-output → evaluate.
    - Templates:
      stage-runner (CPU image flowforge-pipeline-cpu, Java entrypoint with --stage/--args, retries & resources),
      gpu-stage-runner (GPU image flowforge-pipeline-gpu, GPU requests/limits, nodeSelector gpupool, toleration).
  services/orchestrator/src/main/resources/argo/flowforge-pipeline.yaml:
    - Same workflow embedded on classpath for Argo client templating.

3. ARGO WORKFLOW SERVICE & DTOs
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ArgoWorkflowService: @Service in orchestrator; uses RestClient + ArgoProperties:
    - submitPipeline(PipelineRequest): loads YAML template via YAMLFactory, sets spec.arguments.parameters values
      from snapshotId, repoUrls, logTimeRange, runGnn; POSTs to /api/v1/workflows/{ns}; increments
      flowforge.argo.workflow.submitted and returns WorkflowStatus(name, phase, creationTimestamp).
    - getStatus(name): GET /api/v1/workflows/{ns}/{name}, maps to WorkflowStatus.
    - getTaskStatuses(name): GET workflow, inspects status.nodes, returns TaskStatus for Pod-type nodes
      (displayName, phase, timestamps, message).
    - waitForCompletion(name, timeout): polls getStatus every 10s until terminal phase (Succeeded/Failed/Error),
      increments flowforge.argo.workflow.completed with phase tag; throws TimeoutException on deadline.
  DTOs: internal records WorkflowResponse(metadata,status), WorkflowMetadata(name,creationTimestamp),
        WorkflowStatusBody(phase,nodes), WorkflowNodeStatus(type,displayName,phase,startedAt,finishedAt,message),
        and public PipelineRequest, WorkflowStatus, TaskStatus in service package.

4. STAGE RUNNER API (ORCHESTRATOR)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  PipelineController: @RestController at /api/v1/pipelines:
    - POST /api/v1/pipelines → submitPipeline(PipelineRequest) returns 202 Accepted + WorkflowStatus body.
    - GET  /api/v1/pipelines/{name} → getStatus(name).
    - GET  /api/v1/pipelines/{name}/tasks → getTaskStatuses(name).

